  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nOne of our dependencies (`arc-swap` via `slog-scope`) recently had a memory unsafety vulnerability discovered, `RUSTSEC-2020-0091`:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/RustSec/advisory-db/blob/master/crates/arc-swap/RUSTSEC-2020-0091.md\r\n\r\nDetermining whether this is reachable from Lighthouse is an open question.\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nv1.0.4\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nI suspect a `cargo update` will sort us out, as `slog-scope` depends on `arc-swap ^0.4`, so it should just update `arc-swap 0.4.7 -> 0.4.8`. The main question is whether we should consider the v1.0.4 release tainted and immediately release v1.0.5\r\n",
